solution.java:
Here's a Java solution to calculate the `n`-th term of the Fibonacci sequence using recursion:

```java
class Solution {
    public int fibonacci(int n) {
        if (n <= 1) {
            return n;
        }
        return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
    }
}
```

solution.python:
And here's a Python solution to calculate the `n`-th term of the Fibonacci sequence using recursion:

```python
def fibonacci(n):
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2)
```
This Python code calculates the `n`-th term of the Fibonacci sequence using recursion.
